OL,5, Major airlines are charging some       
OL,6, disabled passengers double to fly from 
OL,7, the UK, the BBC has found.             
OL,9,FNearly 30 carriers contacted by the BBC
OL,10,Fsaid passengers with mobility problems 
OL,11,Fmust purchase a full-price ticket for a
OL,12,Fpersonal care assistant (PA).          
OL,14,FThis is despite Civil Aviation         
OL,15,FAuthority guidance on EU law,          
OL,16,Fmaintained by the UK post-Brexit,      
OL,17,Furging airlines to subsidise the cost. 
OL,19,FDisabled people with mobility issues   
OL,20,Fsay the situation is discriminatory.   
